I did some refactoring for this to make the calling code a bit cleaner by adding a factory method to HubSubscriber. Calling code then looks like this:
HubSubscriber subscriber = HubSubscriber.<ApiEndpointStatusChangeEvent>create(eventData -> {
	NetworkStatusEvent.from(eventData).toHubEvent().publish(HubChannel.DATASTORE, Amplify.Hub);
};

HubFilter filter = hubEvent -> {
	return ApiChannelEventName.API_ENDPOINT_STATUS_CHANGED.name().equals(hubEvent.getName());
};

Amplify.Hub.subscribe(HubChannel.API, filter, subscriber);

